MEGAN WONG 
San Mateo, CA | (41 5) 994-1 567 | mwong068@gmail.com | Github: mwong068 | LinkedIn: mwong068 | Portfolio: megan-wong.com

SOFTWARE ENGINEER 
Experience in Ruby on Rails and Javascript based programming and current Software Engineer Intern with a small startup in San Francisco. Former pastry chef who developed hundreds of products from scratch daily and employed adaptability in a fast-paced environment. 2+ years in project management and a knack for conceptualizing and delivering elegant, user-friendly solutions. Excited to connect people through technology after many years of connecting people through food.

TECHNICAL SKILLS 
Ruby, Ruby on Rails, SQL, Javascript, React, Redux, Python, HTML/CSS, Bootstrap, Git

TECHNICAL PROJECTS 
Sweet Spot: Pastry E-Commerce — Live Preview | Github: Front End | Github: Back End 
An 
e-commerce website for pastry chefs to sell their products to people in their communities. ● Implemented user interface employing React, Redux, and Thunk with Material UI for styling ● Incorporated Stripe API to create a fully functional customer checkout experience ● Utilized JSON Web Tokens and localStorage to store encrypted user information client-side 
Pot n'Plot: Virtual Gardening — Live Preview | Github 
A 
virtual gardening website for users to create a garden and populate it with real plant data. ● Built web app entirely with Ruby on Rails following the MVC structure and utilizing bcrypt for authentication ● Made use of Trefle.io API to create plant entries with real-time data
